{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#4737: Nested Teleport of disabled teleport stays in DOM when parent is unmounted",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:27:10.073637+00:00",
  "text": "Nested Teleport of disabled teleport stays in DOM when parent is unmounted\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.19\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[codesandbox.io](https://codesandbox.io/s/dank-https-h3ci5?file=/src/App.vue)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n1. use a teleport, and set it's disabled prop is `true`;\r\n2. put some components inside;\r\n3. make the teleport unmount (e.g. v-if, switch route, or other...);\r\n4. these child components will not be unmount.\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nThese child components will be unmount.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nThese child components will not be unmount.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "scope: teleport"
  ],
